<paragraph id="E663369C9653FFAAFF294217F751BAC5" blockId="1.[136,1452,512,750]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">
The short tuberous rhizome and anther shape of 
<taxonomicName id="21DC4D1F9653FFAAFDFD4217F505BA76" authorityName="N. Krishna &amp; Pradeep, A. Flowering" authorityYear="2021" box="[604,807,512,533]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="murlenensis">
<emphasis id="D4A8EA8E9653FFAAFDFD4217F505BA76" box="[604,807,512,533]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">Begonia murlenensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most closely resemble 
<taxonomicName id="21DC4D1F9653FFAAFBAB4217F280BA76" authorityName="S. H. Huang &amp; Y. M. Shui" authorityYear="1999" box="[1034,1186,512,533]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="manhaoensis">
<emphasis id="D4A8EA8E9653FFAAFBAB4217F280BA76" box="[1034,1186,512,533]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">B. manhaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the new species can be distinguished by its smaller size, lamina being unlobed with brown bulbils and plantlets at the sinus (
<emphasis id="D4A8EA8E9653FFAAFBDC4233F2BABA5A" box="[1149,1176,548,569]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">vs.</emphasis>
shallowly lobed without any bulbils or plantlets at sinus), veins being sparsely scabrous abaxially (
<emphasis id="D4A8EA8E9653FFAAFCFC425FF55ABA3E" box="[861,888,584,605]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">vs.</emphasis>
pubescent-villous). The petioles with only a single groove (
<emphasis id="D4A8EA8E9653FFAAFF64427BF6C2BAE2" box="[197,224,620,641]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">vs.</emphasis>
petiole sulcate with many grooves), and the bracts being oblong-elliptic, 9–14 × 
<quantity id="21249B799653FFAAFC5D427BF26DBAE2" box="[1020,1103,620,642]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6 mm</quantity>
, and pale green (
<emphasis id="D4A8EA8E9653FFAAFB59427BF331BAE2" box="[1272,1299,620,641]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="262">vs.</emphasis>
ovate, 19–23 × 
<quantity id="21249B799653FFAAFF1C4287F739BAC6" box="[189,283,656,678]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" unit="mm" value="12.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="8.0">8–16 mm</quantity>
, reddish)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
