<paragraph id="E663369C9657FFAEFF1C4089F454B947" blockId="5.[136,1452,158,292]" pageId="5" pageNumber="266">
<emphasis id="D4A8EA8E9657FFAEFF1C4089F722B8DB" bold="true" box="[189,256,158,184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="266">Notes</emphasis>
: Plants observed in their natural habitat as well as plants growing at 
<collectingCountry id="9ECB760C9657FFAEFBAE4089F242B8DB" box="[1039,1120,158,184]" name="India" pageId="5" pageNumber="266">Calicut</collectingCountry>
University Botanical Garden consistently have white-silver spotted leaves. The discontinuous, circular, white-silver spotted outline of the lamina is also constant in the observed populations. However, further studies are required to confirm these variegation characters, as they are variable in many other begonias.
</paragraph>
